diff --git a/codex-rs/token-rate-daemon/README.md b/codex-rs/token-rate-daemon/README.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..a2153d4d5553ab860d853eef7e14aaff2ba72e7a
--- /dev/null
+++ b/codex-rs/token-rate-daemon/README.md
@@ -0,0 +1,48 @@
+# Codex live token-rate patch
+
+This local-only patch reports the estimated completion-output rate across every patched Codex
+process using the same Unix datagram socket. User-visible assistant text and streamed tool
+arguments are included; input tokens, hidden reasoning, and tool output are not. Exact usage is
+emitted only when a model response completes.
+
+When a response starts executing tools, the daemon holds that stream's last estimated rate after
+the normal sliding window expires. The held rate is released when all tools from the response
+finish. `tool_active_streams` in the state file reports how many stream rates are currently held.
+
+Build and install from the repository root:
+
+```bash
+cd codex-rs
+cargo build --release --bin codex
+cargo build --release --bin codex-token-rate-daemon
+cd ..
+scripts/install-patched-codex.sh
+```
+
+Start the daemon:
+
+```bash
+SOCKET_PATH="${TMPDIR:-/tmp}/codex-token-rate.sock"
+STATE_FILE="${TMPDIR:-/tmp}/codex-token-rate.json"
+
+~/.local/bin/codex-token-rate-daemon \
+  --socket "$SOCKET_PATH" \
+  --state-file "$STATE_FILE" \
+  --stdout
+```
+
+Start one or more patched Codex sessions in other terminals:
+
+```bash
+export CODEX_TOKEN_RATE_SOCKET="${TMPDIR:-/tmp}/codex-token-rate.sock"
+~/.local/bin/codex-patched
+```
+
+The state file contains the already-aggregated global rate:
+
+```bash
+cat "${TMPDIR:-/tmp}/codex-token-rate.json"
+```
+
+Unset `CODEX_TOKEN_RATE_SOCKET` to disable reporting completely. The sender is nonblocking and
+silently drops events when the daemon is absent.
